After another meltdown, Steve is given pressure from the board and attempts to woo Bill back into the company. Bill finally agrees and Steve has 
a meeting with all the higher ups to have a get to know you session, to better imporve the way the all work together. Then they come to a descion
to terminate all WIP except Phoenix. Many of the other project managers get upset about this but Phoneix does see an improvement as a result. 
Bill and Erik also disccus future plans for when the Phoneix project freeze ends, and how ot maximize work flow with the monitoirng project
as well as configuring a new project managment team to decide project priority. 
